.TH "lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_recover" 9 "lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_recover" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_recover \- Prepare SLI4 device for pci slot recover
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_recover
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is called to prepare the SLI4 device for PCI slot recover. It
aborts all the outstanding SCSI I/Os to the pci device.
